{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/anguttara-nikaya/AN4/66-saragasutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.\nWhat four?\nThe greedy, the hateful, the delusional, and the conceited. </p>\n<p>These are the four people found in the world. </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Full of desire for desirable things, <br>\nenjoying things that seem pleasant, <br>\nbeings shrouded by ignorance, <br>\nonly tighten their bonds. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Born of greed, born of hate, <br>\nborn of delusion: the ignorant <br>\nmake bad karma <br>\nthat afflicts and produces pain. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you act out of these qualities, that’s what you become. <br>\nBut men hindered by ignorance, <br>\nare blind, with no eyes to see, <br>\nand they never imagine that this could be so.” </p>\n</blockquote>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/anguttara-nikaya/AN4/67-ahirajasutta/\">AN.4.67. Ahirājasutta (“The Snake King”)</a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world.\nWhat four?\nThe greedy, the hateful, the delusional, and the conceited. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"These are the four people found in the world. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Full of desire for desirable things, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nenjoying things that seem pleasant, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","val